item.title: HackMidwest 2024: How We Built a USDA Chatbot in 24 Hours (and Won!)
item.description: When my friend and I signed up for HackMidwest 2024, we had no idea what we were going to build. Zero. Zilch. Nada. We showed up with our laptops, a vague sense of excitement, and a whole lot of caffeine. The hackathon kicked off with some awesome workshopsâ€”Red Hat OpenShift, AWS, Pinata, and more. We attended as many as we could, soaking up knowledge and trying to figure out what we could possibly create in 24 hours.
